Titulo: Electrocatalytic Behavior of Calcium Doped LaFeO3 as Cathode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: (X = 0.0, 0.2, 0.4, abbreviated as LCF) as cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC) was synthesized by new route of glycine nitrate method.
Titulo: Electrocatalytic Behavior of Calcium Doped LaFeO3 as Cathode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: LCF materials were characterized by X-ray diffraction (XRD), scanning electron microscopy-energy-dispersive X-ray spectroscopy (SEM-EDX), transmission electron microscopy (TEM), electrical and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS).
Titulo: Electrocatalytic Behavior of Calcium Doped LaFeO3 as Cathode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The powder LCFs exhibited single phase with orthorhombic structure, highly porous and small nanoparticles with average size of 200-300 nm.
Titulo: Electrocatalytic Behavior of Calcium Doped LaFeO3 as Cathode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The electrical conductivities of LCFs increased as increasing the Ca content and achieved the maximum electrical conductivity of 148 Scm(-1) for La0.6Ca0.4FeO3 (X = 0.4) at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrocatalytic Behavior of Calcium Doped LaFeO3 as Cathode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The improved conductivity of LCFs could be a promising cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Electrocatalytic Behavior of Calcium Doped LaFeO3 as Cathode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: In the impedance analysis of fabricated symmetry cell with the optimized La0.6Ca0.4FeO3 cathode and Ce0.8Sm0.2O3 (SDC) electrolyte, the minimum area specific resistance (ASR) of 0.15 Omega cm(2) was observed at 850 degrees C, which may due to the lowest activation energy (1.55 eV), resulting from the reduction of oxygen molecules into oxygen ions.
Titulo: Electrocatalytic Behavior of Calcium Doped LaFeO3 as Cathode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: It was found that calcium doping was essential to increase the charge carrier concentration of lanthanum iron oxide materials, resulting in the high conductivity at intermediate temperature.
Titulo: Electrocatalytic Behavior of Calcium Doped LaFeO3 as Cathode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
